<body>
    <h1>Application Architecture</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <blockquote local-id=3D"bfc1fc0a-0fef-4e93-a32e-3db8f0773fe6">
<style>[data-colorid=3Dfeud6uae6l]{color:#97a0af} html[data-color-mode=3Dda=
rk] [data-colorid=3Dfeud6uae6l]{color:#505968}[data-colorid=3Da2vohdkhkm]{c=
olor:#97a0af} html[data-color-mode=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Da2vohdkhkm]{colo=
r:#505968}</style>
<p local-id=3D"13d7408d-92df-4c5d-9e61-f90bf617bd90"><em>Reference</em></p>
<p local-id=3D"f5be4173-efb9-4daa-884a-6b71e62b91d3">Develop a plan and a r=
oadmap for the architecture for the new software eco-system to answer the a=
forementioned business needs and be useful for the future.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c97e2644-bb5b-49b0-b442-65da40b90fc8"><span class=3D"conflue=
nce-jim-macro jira-issue" data-jira-key=3D"PROD-55583"> <a href=3D"https://=
mcesys.atlassian.net/browse/PROD-55583" class=3D"jira-issue-key"><img class=
=3D"icon" src=3D"https://mcesys.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/v=
iew/type/issuetype/avatar/13909?size=3Dmedium">PROD-55583</a> - <span class=
=3D"summary">Architecture Approach</span> <span class=3D"aui-lozenge aui-lo=
zenge-subtle aui-lozenge-current jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">Pendin=
g</span> </span></p>
</blockquote>
<h2 local-id=3D"dc2bcd5a-1849-46ed-9158-56ab3a4f0cd0" id=3D"ApplicationArch=
itecture-Motivation">Motivation</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ca9591d6-b7b2-4c3c-96e5-b91c29851ed9">Together with MCE=E2=
=80=99s special Metro Retail project, the R&amp;D department raised issues =
of future-proofing MCE=E2=80=99s tech stack, application architecture, and =
workflows =E2=80=94 both developer experience &amp; delivery-to-client. In =
order for us to understand which parts should change, which should go, and =
which should stay, we need to be able to research the reliance on the curre=
nt stack and imagine workflows for the future.</p>
<p local-id=3D"513e75a0-8c2d-4a9e-8280-99b382f72264">Main issues for discus=
sion and research are:</p>
<p local-id=3D"c4608b00-fea1-446d-902b-d13c64676dcb">=E2=80=94 <strong>The =
big why</strong>: how do we envision our future work?</p>
<p local-id=3D"2d68b68c-83a2-4f3c-ad22-9be33556b012">=E2=80=94 <strong>Clie=
nt applications</strong>: architecture, deployment cycle, maintenance cycle=
, extensibility, developer experience.</p>
<p local-id=3D"cbe5ac78-a6f6-4fbc-98af-018c9731f7b0">=E2=80=94 <strong>Refl=
ow flow management</strong>: What=E2=80=99s next for Reflow? Can DTL work o=
utside of reflow? How should the flows be managed? Should there be a future=
 for Reflow=E2=80=99s Trasnports, are they still relevant? Etc. along these=
 lines.</p>
<p local-id=3D"974ffc04-1ed0-4a44-b2b0-aeef3aa90b4b">=E2=80=94 <strong>Conf=
igurable applications</strong>: How and where should we rely on configurati=
on? Who will use the configuration? Should we allow reliance on external co=
nfiguration at all?</p>
<p local-id=3D"61478ac5-feff-49da-bc6a-5e9489ca16d0">=E2=80=94 What=E2=80=
=99s achievable when?</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9d36af89-e9f0-4389-8a44-e6a13e5d5cc8">
<h3 local-id=3D"ce73cfc1-606a-48f8-a300-9ba6e3f191be" id=3D"ApplicationArch=
itecture-QuickTo-DoList">Quick To-Do List</h3>
<ul class=3D"inline-task-list" data-inline-tasks-content-id=3D"4842782721">
<li class=3D"checked" data-inline-task-id=3D"2"><span class=3D"placeholder-=
inline-tasks"><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention current-user-men=
tion" data-account-id=3D"712020:25ff2f21-b239-41a5-a405-fc97ca3c68e0" href=
=3D"https://mcesys.atlassian.net/wiki/people/712020:25ff2f21-b239-41a5-a405=
-fc97ca3c68e0?ref=3Dconfluence" target=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=
=3D"4556390412" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-typ=
e=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://mcesys.atlassian.net/wiki">Yehuda G=
ilead</a> setup meeting with all relevant devs to interview them about thei=
r developer experience.</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"3"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">How =
is configuration being used across the org today IRL.</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"4"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Surv=
ey current status: what metrics should use to measure this?</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"5"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">What=
ever=E2=80=99s not used a lot can be changed/discarded easily.</span></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"9aed6926-387b-4e7a-9bbc-0471e4389622">
<h2 local-id=3D"c7b72680-92a6-4ad7-b327-6eb7749a926c" id=3D"ApplicationArch=
itecture-HowDoWeEnvisionOurFutureWork">How Do We Envision Our Future Work</=
h2>
<ul local-id=3D"8bdc016d-f9a2-4918-89ef-ae803b6d816b">
<li local-id=3D"fe992418-6cf4-4c18-8898-ad5a8d7cf4ee">
<p local-id=3D"f5e0300a-e3a8-4725-b0ae-da7089022645">What is our special br=
and? What do we bring to the engineering table that is rare or special?</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"f485989c-6a78-488e-b0ab-77d1764c77fa">
<p local-id=3D"8d29c108-38b7-4a0c-a6a8-826c02c28500">What is our vision of =
that special MCE quality that we deliver?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5b896f96-fe87-46f1-b5bc-eb14dc99f68c">
<p local-id=3D"805a5b68-7ceb-45c8-8190-ab172d62c4ba">How do we want to expe=
rience our everyday working cycle? Let=E2=80=99s dream about it.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b59a0d32-5cfe-463a-8c81-3225d8c64004">
<p local-id=3D"deeeb116-c99a-4e5e-8b70-5a1bb5bcc9f7">How do we want to adva=
nce on our career path? And where to?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"364647c0-158f-4c13-b66a-96d8bdbf8d75">
<p local-id=3D"96016af5-d72b-46f6-998e-6843ef544845">What are the horizons =
we=E2=80=99d like to explore in the future?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"57ce40ec-83b9-48b5-9b04-17f262a25220">
<p local-id=3D"a771d6b0-ba1f-44e1-b5f3-fcfae5c954ec">How do we envision eng=
ineer involvement in all the stages of the product lifecycle?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"daab3bc0-bec4-49db-8834-d6e44b3efe8d">
<p local-id=3D"ed3ecdea-46c6-42d9-9355-cfb945366e5b">What is a portrait of =
the MCE Senior Engineer?</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4c270674-066f-492d-9a02-7a79605cdd5c">
<p local-id=3D"07224e74-4a69-434f-9022-d885f45238a8">How does our future pr=
oject look?</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"b9a0b21d-d534-491d-abc3-32e7d0495fe8" id=3D"ApplicationArch=
itecture-Thoughts&amp;ConclusionsWIP">Thoughts &amp; Conclusions <span data=
-colorid=3D"a2vohdkhkm">WIP</span></h3>
<p local-id=3D"e7e19f5d-d3de-4473-9118-96ea2e608ce5">=E2=80=94 The Developm=
ent Cycle is a significant part of the entire product production cycle.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6c6f05b8-b360-4939-974f-29f590f90404">=E2=80=94 Engineers sh=
ould be involved in most of the production cycle phases:</p>
<p local-id=3D"be520768-605a-4142-b772-bf22ea296701" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;">=E2=86=92 aware of the business goals</p>
<p local-id=3D"fe37b115-cfbc-4dc0-aad9-96bf426ee20c" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;">=E2=86=92 early in the product decision phase (discovery)</p>
<p local-id=3D"db429faf-7f5c-43a8-b2f6-82a9079d6225" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;">=E2=86=92 have a clear contract with the product &amp; BI about th=
e requirements for engineering</p>
<p local-id=3D"1b72c528-2e7f-4048-9b62-bc50369b6584" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;"><span data-colorid=3D"feud6uae6l">(=E2=86=92 have a clear contract=
 with UX about their version management)</span></p>
<p local-id=3D"9f3af8b9-7370-471a-bede-ee0fc96ac604" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;">=E2=86=92 have a clear Definition of Done of engineering outcomes:=
 that should include usage monitoring, by the engineering team, to ensure t=
hat what was released actually works as expected at the user=E2=80=99s edge=
.</p>
<p local-id=3D"dc76fd51-ecfd-4a1b-ba16-ee73dc5bd95a" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;">=E2=86=92 Draw conclusions based on actual user usage and suggest =
new products to advance the known business direction.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a52f539a-f52b-4689-ace8-c6fa2f5b0258">=E2=80=94 Engineering =
outcomes are measured by two main metrics:</p>
<p local-id=3D"7884b7b3-f684-4460-b0c2-f8bc9959ed5b" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;">=E2=86=92 <strong>Quality</strong> =E2=80=94 this should be unpack=
ed, but in general, we=E2=80=99re talking about maintainability, availabili=
ty &amp; attention to detail.</p>
<p local-id=3D"30f8f85e-95d4-4bf6-bcda-4bb4a8613b00" style=3D"margin-left: =
30.0px;">=E2=86=92 <strong>Velocity</strong> =E2=80=94 how quickly can we r=
ealize stuff with quality, or even how responsive engineering is.</p>
<h3 id=3D"ApplicationArchitecture-Quality">Quality</h3>
<p local-id=3D"52872a03-9460-477a-a8ca-f260a09f3059">What is code quality i=
n a nutshell? Firstly, we need to acknowledge that code is written for two =
different clients: the machine &amp; the human engineer. In terms of the ma=
chine, the code should be bug-free, secure &amp; performant. And in terms o=
f the human, the code should be easily readable, coherently structured, and=
 ready for easy &amp; fast maintenance.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"93e09fd6-973e-4ce5-bd0e-3c52ae9cd002" id=3D"ApplicationArch=
itecture-Velocity">Velocity</h3>
<p local-id=3D"269dffd4-53bc-472f-a9bb-1952c3353b06">Velocity is a metric t=
hat describes the speed at which decisions can be made regarding any specif=
ic code. Be it additions or fixes, bootstrapping or deployment =E2=80=94 in=
 other words =E2=80=94 the ease of moving with a predictable speed from one=
 step of development/deployment to the next. Meaning that it can become ver=
y clear quickly what changes should be made where in order to reach the des=
ired goal.<br>
It=E2=80=99s a great general metric for an engineering team, which is depen=
dent on various factors, like:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bfde3548-e947-4ec3-8359-976e29e8ee70">
<li local-id=3D"2a1f6208-9978-4675-a3c5-b3de46e24122">
<p local-id=3D"d1a701e2-84f1-4d7b-a476-2b6b0358dad4">whether the tasks and =
the goals are clear</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"39d18ba6-93e2-4abd-9d37-85d171941400">
<p local-id=3D"50110fca-0272-4b0d-a217-a77fa9c25cca">whether there are entr=
enched challenges that delay progress</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"03bf7af3-2a8a-4588-aa16-d3cffc1859c1">
<p local-id=3D"a82d91bc-28a5-4202-b26a-4278a475d33c">whether the initial st=
ate of the code is legible and understandable</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b2993730-0da9-4991-8834-ce2d6c2e5b42">
<p local-id=3D"e5fc0fd4-cca3-4908-969e-d04b9d7d40d2">whether there=E2=80=99=
s a clear understanding of how to solve the challenge at hand</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"03d003bb-8bdd-4316-952b-736bf4cab633">
<p local-id=3D"76ca4f64-4c49-4f6b-81a8-78bc43267ca6">Whether there=E2=80=99=
s a safe mechanism to introduce changes</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0cb51c62-6a17-47cb-ad0b-8c91abd4187f">
<p local-id=3D"692fb567-fb0b-438c-97e9-746757660f80">whether there is the r=
equired and suitable tooling for deployment &amp; observability</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"990935ba-42c8-42f8-ba89-16332287ae06">=E2=A0=80In short, if =
you=E2=80=99re healthy, you can have great velocity.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"a2b91b67-d0c7-4ce7-b590-1c1be05e5769" id=3D"ApplicationArch=
itecture-CurrentStatus=E2=80=94DeveloperSurvey">Current Status =E2=80=94 De=
veloper Survey</h2>
<p local-id=3D"7df6f908-81ec-4f3e-a137-0963bfc22dfc"><a data-card-appearanc=
e=3D"inline" href=3D"https://mcesys.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/3695345667/pa=
ges/4942987287/?draftShareId=3D2a045bf5-1c57-4f5a-9c30-b7857ff0de57" local-=
id=3D"707d1f70-76f0-44f3-a256-c06e150a91ad" rel=3D"nofollow">https://mcesys=
.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/3695345667/pages/4942987287/?draftShareId=3D2a04=
5bf5-1c57-4f5a-9c30-b7857ff0de57</a></p>
<h2 local-id=3D"e4e46147-aed3-40bc-b288-2d1b6e8d9fc1" id=3D"ApplicationArch=
itecture-(Client)ApplicationArchitecture">(Client) Application Architecture=
</h2>
<p>A bucket list of important ideas &amp; themes.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"94006563-793e-4570-b68d-eb400a2cc902">
<li local-id=3D"39f94502-519e-40af-956c-2fc1e3c50a20">
<p local-id=3D"5877cc15-8284-4fe5-acf6-88c551e41fed">My opinions on this ma=
tter are rather clear: <br>
=E2=80=94 stupid parts<br>
=E2=80=94 declarative<br>
=E2=80=94 global state<br>
=E2=80=94 each project is an entire application (and this is how it=E2=80=
=99s viewed)<br>
=E2=80=94 configuration in code<br>
=E2=80=94 Each project is a unique butterfly<br>
=E2=80=94 a great set of rules and best practices, that keeps things simple=
, and allows a lot of creativity<br>
=E2=80=94 GOAL: amazing maintenance</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"474c837a-624e-41f6-b3b5-4aea9a3a938f">
<p local-id=3D"816dbb49-3615-4b64-a703-135039b239f5">Eli=E2=80=99s ideal: a=
llow MCE engineering to enjoy a startup-engineering culture:<br>
=E2=80=94 Easy beginnings<br>
=E2=80=94 Freedom of =E2=80=9Cmovement=E2=80=9D &amp; tool/architecture cho=
ice<br>
=E2=80=94 Loose coupling<br>
=E2=80=94 Simple black-box components that do one thing!<br>
=E2=80=94 Industry adopted tech and practices</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8336adfe-a43a-4d82-a1df-3a46f6b21599">
<p local-id=3D"63cfd66c-22a9-4624-993b-1567e67fce6b">Current, but well-weat=
hered</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e1140afd-90aa-4255-a54b-f32bf7bfcb3f">
<p local-id=3D"6a41aeef-fa44-4afb-b1bf-91504192aa9b">I LOOOOOOOVE Redux =E2=
=80=94 it=E2=80=99s a great paradigm if you know how to use it.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6d91e1b9-ac2d-42c1-bb1b-f60c93cc0c37">
<p local-id=3D"074ab0cc-8ec5-4346-8e75-d837432a3b13">Reactive UI</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a5367ff6-26b1-4756-b408-2c7b3316a8c0">
<p local-id=3D"5e803439-24e0-49a5-bd51-827d8191dc04">Smart &amp; homegrown =
design systems</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f2eb6be9-ebf3-48e8-8b29-f0769240a881">
<p local-id=3D"4756aac5-0a55-44b8-a026-c882ed09d5a1">AUTOMATION!!!</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1c2e1259-a272-4b07-b6f4-4becf3969bdd">
<p local-id=3D"10250123-e8c5-4631-b587-f601a9c055d5">Find the balance betwe=
en global uniformity of architecture &amp; freedom of tools and technologie=
s used in our projects.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1dcc9009-47c8-4eb0-b621-6f8182d2a013">
<p local-id=3D"95261aec-f3cb-4c4d-8823-3bed866befad">Optimized for user exp=
erience!<br>
=E2=80=94 meaning we should monitor usage and be in the loop directly, and =
not only through CSMs or Product people.<br>
=E2=80=94 Prioritize great UX planning and demand that UX people deliver hi=
gh-standard specs<br>
=E2=80=94 Performance (&amp; perceived performance) is part of our definiti=
on of done.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<div id=3D"expander-705552675" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-705552675" class=3D"expand-control">
